parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration caused by a frozen throttle linkage can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
unintended acceleration
stuck throttle
inability to slow down or stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak in the trunk compartment can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to a vehicle fire or explosion, especially in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Strong gasoline smell coming from the trunk compartment
fuel spillage inside the trunk
fuel dripping or leaking from the trunk area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Coil Spring Support Bracket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring support bracket can cause the coil spring to become dislodged, leading to loss of vehicle control, uneven tire wear, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Cracks or breaks in the front support bracket
uneven ride
clunking or rattling noise from the front suspension
uneven tire wear
loss of vehicle stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brake skipping or grabbing issue can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, especially when driving down hills or inclines.
symptoms: The brakes skip or grab when backing up
especially on slight hills or inclines
requiring the driver to pump the brake pedal to stop the vehicle
uneven or spongy brake pedal feel
rear wheels lock up or vibrate when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, it can also result in a total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell inside the cabin
smoke billowing from the hood
visible flames under the hood.
